title: Huntley & Palmers "Albert" Biscuit
provenance: Collection of Carol B. Brener and Stephen W. Brener
description: Circular, in the form of a biscuit, with small, dot-like, simulated perforations on front surface, inscribed "Huntley & Palmers," "Albert." On reverse are small, vertical and horizontal, dash-like, simulated perforations. Outer circumference of box displays irregular, scratch-like marks in surface. Lid, or upper portion of biscuit, hinged on back. Striker on bottom edge.
name: Matchsafe
